Helper functions

In [3]:
def lookupCols(df, lookup_df, key_col, cols):
    return df.join(lookup_df[cols], on=key_col, lsuffix='', rsuffix='_lookup')

def filterYears(df, minYear=2022, maxYear=2024):
    return df[(df['year'] >= minYear) & (df['year'] <= maxYear)]

def getRaceId(year, raceName):  
    race = races[(races['year'] == year) & (races['name'] == raceName)]
    if not race.empty:
        raceId = race.index[0]
        return raceId
    else:
        raise ValueError(f"No race found for {raceName} in {year}")

Starting grid vs final position¶

In [6]:
def plotRs(year, raceName):

    raceId = getRaceId(year, raceName)
    gridVsFinish = results[results['raceId'] == raceId].copy()
    gridVsFinish = lookupCols(gridVsFinish, drivers, 'driverId', ['code'])
    gridVsFinish = lookupCols(gridVsFinish, constructors, 'constructorId', ['name'])

    # Starts from pit lane are recorded as grid=0. Replace 0 with max grid + 1
    gridVsFinish['gridClean'] = gridVsFinish['grid'].replace(0, gridVsFinish['grid'].max() + 1)

    # Exclude retirements for rs calculation
    gridVsFinishFinishers = gridVsFinish[gridVsFinish['positionText'].str.isnumeric()]

    corr, _ = stats.spearmanr(gridVsFinishFinishers['gridClean'], gridVsFinishFinishers['positionOrder'])
    print(f"Spearman correlation between grid position and finishing position: {corr:.2f}")

    ax = sns.scatterplot(
        data=gridVsFinishFinishers, 
        x='gridClean', 
        y='positionOrder', 
        hue='name', 
        palette=constructorPalette,
        s=100
    )

    for _, row in gridVsFinishFinishers.iterrows():
        ax.text(row['gridClean'] - 0.35, row['positionOrder'] + 0.1, row['code'], fontsize=7)

    ax.set_title(f"{raceName} {year}: Grid vs Finishing Positions ($r_s$ = {corr:.2f})")
    ax.set_xlabel("Starting Grid Position")
    ax.set_ylabel("Finishing Race Position")
    ax.invert_xaxis()
    ax.invert_yaxis()
    ax.set_xticks(range(1, gridVsFinishFinishers['gridClean'].max() + 1))
    ax.set_yticks(range(1, gridVsFinishFinishers['positionOrder'].max() + 1))

    plt.legend(title='Constructor', bbox_to_anchor=(1.05, 1), loc='upper left')
    plt.tight_layout()
    plt.show()

def plotPosD(year, raceName):

    raceId = getRaceId(year, raceName)
    gridVsFinish = results[results['raceId'] == raceId].copy()
    gridVsFinish = lookupCols(gridVsFinish, drivers, 'driverId', ['code'])
    gridVsFinish = lookupCols(gridVsFinish, constructors, 'constructorId', ['name'])

    # Starts from pit lane are recorded as grid=0. Replace 0 with max grid + 1
    gridVsFinish['gridClean'] = gridVsFinish['grid'].replace(0, gridVsFinish['grid'].max() + 1)

    # Calculate grid position changes
    gridVsFinish['positionChange'] = gridVsFinish['gridClean'] - gridVsFinish['positionOrder']
    gridVsFinishSorted = gridVsFinish.sort_values('positionChange')

    ax = sns.barplot(
        data=gridVsFinishSorted, 
        x='positionChange', 
        y='code', 
        hue='name', 
        palette=constructorPalette, 
        dodge=False
    )

    ax.set_xlabel('Grid Position Change')
    ax.set_ylabel('Driver')
    ax.set_title(f'{raceName} {year}: Grid Position Changes')
    ax.invert_yaxis()
    ax.set_xticks(range(int(gridVsFinish['positionChange'].min()) - 1, int(gridVsFinish['positionChange'].max()) + 2, 2))
    ax.axvline(x=0, color='black', linestyle='-', linewidth=0.8)
    plt.legend(title='Constructor', bbox_to_anchor=(1.05, 1), loc='upper left')

    plt.tight_layout()
    plt.show()

minYear, maxYear = 2022, 2024

resultsYear = lookupCols(results, races, 'raceId', ['year'])
resultsRegs = filterYears(resultsYear, minYear, maxYear).copy()

# Starts from pit lane are recorded as grid=0. Replace 0 with max grid + 1
resultsRegs.loc[:, 'gridClean'] = (
    resultsRegs
    .groupby('raceId')['grid']
    .transform(lambda x: x.replace(0, x.max() + 1))
)

# Exclude retirements for rs calculation (Keep for position change)
resultsRegsFinishers = resultsRegs.loc[
    resultsRegs['positionText'].str.isnumeric()
].copy()
In [11]:
corrByRace = (
    resultsRegsFinishers
    .groupby('raceId')
    .apply(lambda x: stats.spearmanr(x['gridClean'], x['positionOrder'])[0] if len(x) > 2 else None)
    .rename('correlation') 
    .reset_index()
)

corrByRace = lookupCols(corrByRace, races, 'raceId', ['circuitId', 'year'])
corrByRace = lookupCols(corrByRace, circuits, 'circuitId', ['location'])

corrByCircuit = corrByRace.groupby('location')['correlation'].mean().reset_index()
corrByCircuit = corrByCircuit.sort_values('correlation', ascending=False)

ax = sns.barplot(
    data=corrByCircuit,
    x='correlation',
    y='location',
    palette='coolwarm_r'
)

ax.set_xlabel('Average Spearman Correlation')
ax.set_ylabel('Circuit Location')
ax.set_title(f'Grid-to-Finish Correlation by Circuit ({minYear}-{maxYear})')
ax.axvline(x=0, color='black', linestyle='-', linewidth=0.8)

plt.tight_layout()
plt.show()

Number of overtakes (estimate)

In [14]:
def plotOvertakes(year, raceName):
    raceId = getRaceId(year, raceName)
    raceLapTimes = lapTimes.loc[raceId].copy()

    # Pivot to get position by driver and lap
    positions = raceLapTimes.pivot_table(
        index='lap', 
        columns='driverId', 
        values='position'
    )

    # Count overtakes: position improvements (position decreases, since lower is better)
    overtakes = (
        (positions.diff() < 0)
        .sum()
        .rename('numOvertakes')
        .reset_index()
    )

    # Add driver codes and constructor names
    driverConstructors = results.loc[results['raceId'] == raceId, ['driverId', 'constructorId']].set_index('driverId')
    overtakes = lookupCols(overtakes, drivers, 'driverId', ['code'])
    overtakes = lookupCols(overtakes, driverConstructors, 'driverId', ['constructorId'])
    overtakes = lookupCols(overtakes, constructors, 'constructorId', ['name']).sort_values('numOvertakes', ascending=False)
    
    totalOvertakes = overtakes['numOvertakes'].sum()
    
    ax = sns.barplot(
        data=overtakes,
        x='numOvertakes',
        y='code',
        hue='name',
        palette=constructorPalette,
        dodge=False
    )

    ax.set_xlabel('Number of Overtakes')
    ax.set_ylabel('Driver')
    ax.set_title(f'{raceName} {year} - Overtakes by Driver (Total: {int(totalOvertakes)})')
    ax.legend(title='Constructor', bbox_to_anchor=(1.05, 1), loc='upper left')

    plt.tight_layout()
    plt.show()

# Calculate average overtakes by circuit over years
overtakesByRace = []

for raceId in resultsRegs['raceId'].unique():
    raceLapTimes = lapTimes.loc[raceId].copy()
    
    # Pivot to get position by driver and lap
    positions = raceLapTimes.pivot_table(
        index='lap', 
        columns='driverId', 
        values='position'
    )
    
    # Count total overtakes for this race
    totalOvertakes = (positions.diff() < 0).sum().sum()
    
    overtakesByRace.append({
        'raceId': raceId,
        'totalOvertakes': totalOvertakes
    })


overtakesByRace = pd.DataFrame(overtakesByRace)

# Join with race and circuit info
overtakesByRace = lookupCols(overtakesByRace, races, 'raceId', ['circuitId', 'year'])
overtakesByRace = lookupCols(overtakesByRace, circuits, 'circuitId', ['location'])

# Calculate average overtakes by circuit
overtakesByCircuit = (
    overtakesByRace
    .groupby('location')['totalOvertakes']
    .mean()
    .reset_index()
    .sort_values('totalOvertakes', ascending=False)
)

# Plot
ax = sns.barplot(
    data=overtakesByCircuit,
    x='totalOvertakes',
    y='location',
    palette='coolwarm'
)

ax.set_xlabel('Average Number of Overtakes')
ax.set_ylabel('Circuit Location')
ax.set_title(f'Average Overtakes by Circuit ({minYear}-{maxYear})')
ax.invert_yaxis()

plt.tight_layout()
plt.show()
